===Etymology===
[[File:Indus_river.svg|thumb|Punjab is named after five tributaries of the Indus River]]
From {{etyl|fa}} {{term|sc=fa-Arab|پنجاب||[Land of] the Five Rivers|tr=panj-âb|lang=fa}}, from {{term|sc=fa-Arab|پنج|tr=panj|lang=fa||five}} and {{term|sc=fa-Arab|آب||tr=âb|water|lang=fa}}, referring to five rivers of the {{w|Punjab region}}: the [[w:Jhelum River|Jhelum]], the [[w:Chenab River|Chenab]], the [[w:Ravi River|Ravi]], the {{w|Sutlej}} and the [[w:Beas River|Beas]].

